.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
provides the public C API used by the
.Xr mport 1
package manager and related tools.
It supports repository access, package installation and removal, metadata
queries, verification, auditing, settings management, and package creation.
.Pp
Applications should include only
.In mport.h .
The private header
.In mport_private.h
is an internal implementation detail and is not part of the supported public
API.
.Pp
Typical programs begin by creating and initializing an
.Vt mportInstance
with
.Fn mport_instance_new
and
.Fn mport_instance_init ,
then install any desired callbacks with
.Fn mport_set_msg_cb ,
.Fn mport_set_progress_init_cb ,
.Fn mport_set_progress_step_cb ,
.Fn mport_set_progress_free_cb ,
or
.Fn mport_set_confirm_cb .
When all work is complete, release library resources with
.Fn mport_instance_free .
.Pp
Most functions return one of the following status codes defined in
.In mport.h :
.Bl -tag -width ".Dv MPORT_ERR_FATAL"
.It Dv MPORT_OK
The operation completed successfully.
.It Dv MPORT_ERR_FATAL
The operation failed.
Detailed error text is available from
.Fn mport_err_string .
.It Dv MPORT_ERR_WARN
The operation completed with a warning.
.El
.Pp
Functions returning dynamically allocated strings, vectors, or structures
transfer ownership to the caller unless otherwise documented.
Use the matching free helpers such as
.Fn mport_pkgmeta_vec_free ,
.Fn mport_index_entry_free_vec ,
.Fn mport_index_mirror_entry_free_vec ,
.Fn mport_index_depends_free_vec ,
.Fn mport_assetlist_free ,
.Fn mport_createextras_free ,
or
.Fn mport_stats_free
when they are available.
